<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Lithium Carbonate Medical Tablets Market</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Regulatory Hurdles:</strong> The stringent regulations imposed by various health authorities can delay the introduction of new lithium carbonate formulations. Compliance with good manufacturing practices (GMP) and quality assurance standards is demanding and can be costly.</li>        <li><strong>Side Effects and Patient Compliance:</strong> Lithium carbonate is associated with several side effects including weight gain, thyroid dysfunction, and renal implications. These side effects can lead to non-compliance among patients who may struggle with the treatment's adverse effects.</li>        <li><strong>Market Competition:</strong> The presence of multiple pharmaceutical companies producing generic versions of lithium carbonate tablets intensifies competition, resulting in potential price wars that can erode profit margins.</li>        <li><strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong> The supply chain for both raw materials and finished products can be affected by geopolitical factors and pandemics, leading to insufficient product availability in the market.</li>        <li><strong>Public Perception:</strong> The stigma surrounding mental health treatment can affect market growth, as patients may avoid seeking treatment or might have negative perceptions of lithium therapy.</li>    </ul>        <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Research and Development:</strong> There is a growing demand for innovative drug delivery systems and formulations that minimize side effects and enhance patient adherence. Investing in R&D could lead to the development of sustained-release or combination therapies that make treatment more manageable.</li>        <li><strong>Telemedicine Integration:</strong> The rise in telehealth services offers opportunities for improved patient monitoring and consultations, enhancing the adherence to lithium carbo